				</div>
				<div class='excerpt'><p>Our family vacation has come to an end, but we built some wonderful new memories in the family togetherness, skiing&#8230;and eating realm. Friday, Marlboro Man and I left our skis on the rack and spent the morning together. Breakfast was at the top of the list. &nbsp; We settled on this place in Lionshead Village&#8230;and it really is a little diner! &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Here&#8217;s the inside. No tables, just a three-sided eating bar wrapped&hellip;<a class="more-link" href="http://thepioneerwoman.com/cooking/2012/03/my-last-breakfast-in-colorado/" title="Continue reading My Last Breakfast in Colorado" class="keep-reading">Keep Reading &rarr;</a></p></div><div class="clr"></div>		</div>
